# Consumer styling — keep docs in sync

When changing **consumer styling policy**, **layout primitives**, **screen patterns**, **recipes**, **guardrails**, or **`tollerud-ui-audit`**, update the related files in the **same commit**. Do not update only the docs app or only markdown — agents and humans read both.

## File roles

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `SKILL.md` | **Source of truth for agents** — exports, recipes table, guardrails, gotchas |
| `AGENTS.md` | Contributor + agent guide — import blocks, reference table, release checklist |
| `GETTING_STARTED.md` | **Shipped in npm** — install, policy, checklist, audit command |
| `COMPLETENESS_ROADMAP.md` | Open roadmap items; update on release when scope changes |
| `CHANGELOG.md` | User-facing release notes (docs site parses this at runtime) |
| `COMPONENTS.md` | Human usage index — link to Recipes, policy, and audit command |
| `README.md` | Repo landing — install pointer and audit one-liner |
| `CONTRIBUTING.md` | Contributor sync matrix (this rule mirrors it) |

Completed consumer styling initiative (archived): [docs/archive/CONSUMER_STYLING_ROADMAP.md](docs/archive/CONSUMER_STYLING_ROADMAP.md).

## Docs app (live site)

| Area | Files |
|------|-------|
| New docs route | `docs-app/lib/docs-routes.js`, `docs-app/components/docs-shell.jsx` |
| Section deep links / ⌘K | `docs-app/lib/component-catalog.js` |
| Recipes | `docs-app/components/pages/page-recipes.jsx` |
| Screen patterns | `docs-app/components/pages/page-screens.jsx` |
| Layout primitives | `docs-app/components/pages/page-layout.jsx` |
| Getting started mirror | `docs-app/components/pages/page-getting-started.jsx` |
| Guides / checklist | `docs-app/components/pages/page-resources.jsx` |
| Overview audit CTA | `docs-app/components/pages/page-overview.jsx` |

New nav entries need `PAGE_TITLES` and, if the page uses `go()`, add the route id to `PAGES_WITH_GO` in `docs-shell.jsx`.

## Audit script

If you change `scripts/audit-consumer-styling.mjs` or the `tollerud-ui-audit` bin in `package.json`:

1. Document behavior in `GETTING_STARTED.md` → Consumer project checklist (include error codes, `--warn-only`, alternative invocation)
2. Mirror commands in `SKILL.md` → Consumer guardrails, `AGENTS.md` reference table, `COMPONENTS.md`, `README.md`, and docs pages (`page-getting-started.jsx`, `page-resources.jsx`, `page-overview.jsx`)
3. Run `npm run test:consumer-styling` — must pass on `fixtures/consumer` and `examples/next-starter`
4. Note the change in `CHANGELOG.md`

## New components (layout / screen patterns)

Follow [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) §2–4 **plus** consumer styling rows in [CONTRIBUTING.md](CONTRIBUTING.md):

- Demo on `page-layout.jsx` or `page-screens.jsx` (prefer live `<Demo>` over code-only snippets)
- Optional recipe snippet on `page-recipes.jsx` if it is a common full-page pattern
- `SKILL.md` catalog entry with props summary
- Deep link in `component-catalog.js`

## Do not

- Update `SKILL.md` without checking `components/index.ts` exports still match
- Add docs-only guidance to `SKILL.md` without mirroring key points in `GETTING_STARTED.md` when consumers need it offline
- Edit `docs-app/public/CHANGELOG.md` directly — it is copied from root `CHANGELOG.md` on `npm run build:docs`

## Before push

```bash
npm run test:consumer-styling
npm run build:docs
npm run validate   # full gate before release PRs
```
